IBADAN – A chieftain of All Progressives Congress (APC) in Oyo state, Hon Akinjide Akinola has advised all the party members, stakeholders and gladiators to put party supremacy and interest above personal ambitions, which is the major trademark of real progressive. Akinola, who is an aspirant for Egbeda/Ona Ara Federal House of Representative, tasked them to drop their ambitions and think as a progressive family. Speaking with journalists in Ibadan, he also tasked leaders and stakeholders of the Oyo APC to come together as a united family to resolve various issues within the party. Akume’s Birthday: APC Officials At Daggers Drawn Over… Saraki Not Your Problem, Deliver Your Promises To Kwara People,… Akinola said what should be their priority now is to focus ultimately on how to sweep all positions in the 2023 general elections at all levels in the state. Speaking on the crisis within the party, Akinola expressed optimism that the party will come together as one, especially when the time for elections is near. The House of Representatives hopeful asserted confidence that the present crisis in his party will not affect the fortunes of the APC in the 2023 election. He said, “My appeal to the leaders of the party is for everyone to come together as a family. We are their foot soldiers. If our leaders come together as one, which they are already doing, the issues will be resolved. “At the national level, there is already a reconciliation committee and I can assure you that, in a few days, everything will be resolved. Everybody should drop ambition, let us think as a progressive force; let us think asa family and we will achieve what we want. POLL “The current issues in the Oyo APC won’t affect our fortunes in the 2023 election. EventhePDPin the state has its issues; every party has its issues. When the time comes, we will come together as a family and resolve the issues. APC is a progressive family.